To Run Enumeration, Enumeration of Topological Order and PERT Codes:
              Compile source code using JAVA IDE
    a. create a simple java project in your favorite IDE(Eclipse, Netbeans, IntellijIDEA)
    b. copy the netid package folder inside the src folder
    c. build the project using the given functionality provided in your IDE
    d.(1). execute the main method in Enumerate.java OR EnumerateTopological.java file.
    d.(2). To Run Pert.java: execute the main method in LP4Driver.java file.             
 
              Run via Command line :
              a. Unzip sxm180018
              b. Go to parent folder of unzipped sxm180018
              c.(1). Compile : javac sxm180018/Enumerate.java OR javac sxm180018/EnumerateTopological.java
              c.(2). For PERT.java - Complile : javac sxm180018/LP4Driver.java
              d.(1). Run : java sxm180018.Enumerate OR java sxm180018.EnumerateTopological
              d.(2). For PERT: Run java sxm180018.LP4Driver
             
 
Graph.java, DFS.java,LP4Driver.java and Timer.java should be placed in same package as PERT.java
 
EnumerateTopological.java:
              - EnumerateTopological.java calls permute() method of Enumerate.java
              - Class Selector extends Approver class of Enumerate.java and overrides select, unselect and visit methods.
              - a new method 'init()' is created to get indegree of each vertex.
             
PERT.java:
	LP4Driver calls static pert() method from PERT.java.
	In case of file as input, provide the path\filename [space] 1 in the command line 	or follow following steps in IDE
		1. Build the project
		2. Open Edit configurations
		3. click + in left pane
		4. select java application
		5. Provide above input in program arguments box.
		6. Click apply and ok.
  